NOTE: yum pacakge mailx is required on remote server


https://support.lenovo.com/us/en/solutions/lnvo-dsa



DRIVERS
# SCSI device info
lsmod | grep sg
# BCM device info
lsmod | grep tg3
# LSI RAID info
lsmod | grep mptctl

CMDLINE OPTIONS
-?, -h            Display help for DSA command-line options.

-b                Run in batch mode.

-d <DIR>          Create output files in DIR
                  Default is /var/log/IBM_Support

-diags            Execute all non-destructive diagnostic tests.

--extract <dir>   Extract DSA executable files into a designated directory
                  (Use <dir>/collectall to launch DSA)

-html <dir>       Specify HTML output directory.

-ibmid            Users provides their IBM Identifier. Work with -upload.

--ipmi-lan <userid:password@IP [:port]>
                  Collect IPMI log via Out-Of-Band mode.

-text             Create TEXT output files.

-upload           Upload DSA output to SRSP and ISP by ecc common client C++ API.

-v                Create HTML output files.

-x                Do not create a compressed XML file.
